The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, March 06, 2004 				 Mehta bail
																								New Delhi, March 5 (PTI): Delhi High Court has rejected the anticipatory bail application of film maker Ketan Mehta, accused of cheating Prasar Bharati of over Rs 13 crore in the telecast of a programme.Mehtas bail plea was rejected by Justice O.P. Dwivedi.																								Besides Mehta, the director of Maya Entertainment, the other accused are Neelesh S. Dalal, the director of Shree Madhav Polyproduct and Trading Pvt. Ltd, Babu Sapte, K. Venkataram and Ashok Jalan, all directors of Stellar Communication.																								A case was registered against them under Section 406 (criminal breach of trust), Section 420 (cheating) and Section 120-B (criminal conspiracy) of the IPC.																								Prasar Bharati had alleged that the accused had induced it to telecast their programme Truck Dhina Dhin on DD-I by giving a bank guarantee of Western Co-operative Bank Ltd, Mumbai, of Rs 12.10 crore.
